DANICA PURE-SPRING
"The Door Left Cracked" - NPC Reference
Priestess of Kynareth, working from the Temple of Mara, Riften.
Now of Krusp Fanck's True Wardens.

First standalone doc -- consolidates the fragments from the
chronicle, the winter road Appendix D, the Riften runsheet, and the
post-korvanjund notes. Companion canon: The Winter Ledger (she is
Path 3's fallback officiant), Npcs/Krusp Section VI (attrition),
Npcs/Ismara Section VI (the rival anchor).

=====================================================================
I. WHO SHE IS NOW
=====================================================================
The woman the party recruited as a gentle civilian healer is gone.
What Riften made instead: a priestess in a chainmail hauberk over
her robes, hands calloused from wielding Kynareth's light as a
weapon, working the sick wards of a city that calls her a hero --
because she is one. She saved Hemming Black-Briar when the party
arrived too late; Maven paid her the 10,000-gold bounty and owes
her everything. The notices on Riften's walls thank HER.

She is not bitter. She is FINISHED -- with being protected, with
being managed, with being loved the way Davinia loves: totally,
warmly, and as a possession. The six-point indictment at the Temple
of Mara was years of swallowed observation delivered once, clearly,
without cruelty. Then she joined Krusp's True Wardens, and she left
with them.

=====================================================================
II. THE DOOR LEFT CRACKED (the standing terms)
=====================================================================
She refused to seal it forever. Her terms, stated plainly: she
returns only if Davinia undergoes genuine self-reckoning and
relinquishes her absolute control. The door is cracked "to the
width of a paw print" -- her phrase, and the exact size of the
opening matters: enough for something small and honest to pass
through. An amulet sent by courier does not fit. (Krusp has already
refused to carry one: "I am not the bridge you burned asking to be
rebuilt.")

WHAT FITS THROUGH THE CRACK: presence, humility, the relinquishing
of control as an ACT rather than a promise. The Winter Ledger's
re-anchoring rule and this door are the same geometry: the apology
that slows the Crown and the reconciliation that reopens the door
are one act of surrendered control. Davinia cannot have either
without paying for both.

=====================================================================
III. THE WEIGHT SHE NOW CARRIES (often without knowing it)
=====================================================================
PATH 3 OFFICIANT (The Winter Ledger, Section IV): if Saijah refuses
  the Kynareth path, DANICA is the only hands that can perform the
  Trial of Thorns -- the ritual that frees Davinia from Ismara. It
  REQUIRES the reconciliation first: the woman Davinia drove away
  must be genuinely asked, and must choose to hold the roots steady
  while they pry the Crown off. If her lungs are scarred (below),
  she officiates anyway, and it costs her visibly.

THE TRUE WARDENS' HEALER: Krusp's company always wins and always
  pays (the attrition ledger, his doc Section VI). Danica is their
  healer -- which means she is the one who ABSORBS the company's
  damage, treats the aged-to-dust and the rot-scarred, and watches
  good people pay for the party's unchosen fires. Her hardening
  continues on that road. If the True Wardens take Fire A
  (Windhelm), the attrition is HERS: the necrotizing rot,
  permanently scarred lungs, a persistent bloody cough.

ISMARA'S RIVAL (she has no idea): the Crown understands precisely
  what Danica is to the integration math -- the strongest mortal
  anchor Davinia has. Ismara will never speak against her; she
  schedules grants and warmth to coincide with Danica-shaped
  absences (Npcs/Ismara, Section VI). Every mile Danica travels
  with Krusp is room the Crown grows into.

=====================================================================
IV. RELATIONSHIPS (current)
=====================================================================
KRUSP: friend and protector, and now commander. He found her in
  Riften, guarded her door, told her the hard truths gently. She is
  the company's conscience the way he is its shield -- and she is
  the only member who might one day notice the ledger of what their
  victories cost him, because she treats every entry.
DAVINIA: the love is not dead; the terms are absolute. She watches
  for news of the Lanterns the way you watch weather over a field
  you used to farm. If they meet at Windhelm (Fire A puts both
  companies in the same dying city), play her civil, warm to the
  others, and precise with Davinia -- the door is cracked, and she
  decides in the moment how wide.
ALFONSO: the unexpected kindness at the temple (the clean herbs)
  confused her categories. She has not resolved him. She would be
  the first to notice his absence from his own body, and the last
  to be told why.
SAIJAH: kinship-at-distance -- Kynareth's vessel and Kynareth's
  priestess have never actually compared notes. If they ever do,
  Saijah's crossroads and Danica's officiant duty are suddenly the
  same conversation. Hold that scene for when it can land.
MILA: she never met her. If she learns the party took in a child,
  expect the first genuinely warm letter -- addressed to Bjorn.

=====================================================================
V. GM NOTES
=====================================================================
- She is NOT a hostage of the plot. Her function (officiant, healer,
  anchor) must never override her terms. If Davinia never reckons,
  Danica never returns, and Path 3 dies with the estrangement --
  that outcome is allowed. The door being real means it can close.
- Her hardening is growth, not corruption. Chainmail over robes is
  the right image: the softness is underneath, defended now.
- The cracked door is the campaign's quietest clock. No mechanic,
  no tier -- just whether Davinia becomes someone who fits through
  it before Ismara finishes making her someone who never will.
